      "content": "that's a good start. i want to make sure the essay doesn't sound like it's just ignoring the other side, but i want the counter-arguments to look weak. can you write a paragraph that brings up the 'meritocracy' argument or the idea that redistribution is 'unfair', but then immediately shuts it down by showing why those views are basically just excuses for maintaining the status quo?",
